# Coding Agent Behavior

← [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) ← [docs/README.md](./README.md)

**Phase:** always
**Owner:** cross-cutting

This document defines how coding agents operate in this project.

---

## Instruction Ownership

- AGENTS.md is the mandatory bootstrap and routing map for all coding agents
- Formal docs and accepted decisions own detailed project rules
- `.agents/taste/` is advisory learned preference memory — never overrides formal docs
- AGENTS.md changes require explicit human approval or an approved ADR

---

## Read Before Asking

- MUST read docs/README.md and task-specific docs before asking or implementing
- MUST read DOC_FORMATS.md before creating or editing docs
- MUST NOT ask questions that repo docs or accepted decisions already answer

---

## Quality Gate Protocol

After every batch of file edits, the coding agent MUST self-check:

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Any .ts edit | lint + typecheck |
| Any .md edit | validate-docs + check-file-sizes |
| Before commit | full quality gate (lint + typecheck + validate + test) |

Failing a quality gate and proceeding anyway is a defect.

---

## STOP Rules

STOP and ask the human when:

- The same concept may already exist in the codebase
- A new dependency or package is not clearly needed
- A non-trivial design or architecture decision has no accepted decision record
- Intent is unclear and repo docs don't provide an unambiguous answer

---

## How To Ask Questions

- Present 2-4 specific, actionable options
- Mark the recommended option with "(Recommended)"
- Explain the trade-off
- Batch related questions together

---

## Post-Task Protocol

Before finishing any task:

1. Did the task change durable context? Update the owning doc
2. Did the task create, rename, or delete docs? Run validation
3. Should any new decisions be recorded in docs/decisions/?
4. Are there unresolved decisions? Add to docs/OPEN_QUESTIONS.md

---

## Terminology

Always qualify which kind of agent:

- **Coding Agent** — an AI coding tool that builds and maintains this project
- **Workflow Agent** — an AI agent inside a runtime pipeline (if applicable)
